text: Obstetric ultrasonography, or prenatal ultrasound, is the use of medical ultrasonography in pregnancy, in which sound waves are used to create real- time visual images of the developing embryo or fetus in the uterus (womb). == Related pages == * Ultrasound (3D) Category:ultrasonography Category:Medical imaging in pregnancy Category:Obstetrics and gynecology Category:Pregnancy and childbirth
title: Obstetric ultrasonography
